         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1967a"/><citedRange>66</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... in just such lineage as Buddha (by the name of Śākyamuni). May my father be the king by the name of Śuddhodana, my mother</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a1 #a2 #a3 #a4 #a5 #a6 #b1 #b2 #b3 #b4 #b5 #b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:sieg1944"/><citedRange>29</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:ogihara2010"/><citedRange>173</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Mahāmāyā by name, (my spouse) Yaśodharā (?) by name, my son Rāhula by name, Ānanda my servant, Śāriputra [and] Maudgalyāyana</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">shall be the nobles pair of my pupils. (1. With a love)ly voice the Buddha, the master, says: stand up, stand up, [my] son, you</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3 #a4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>308</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">(certainly,) afterwards in the life of men [lasting] (120) years, will be the Tathāgata Śākyamuni, the Arhat,</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>294</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1968"/><citedRange>223</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">the Buddha truly knowing all dharmas together. As you have wished, so indeed it shall be.</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>102</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1969"/><citedRange>260</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... You will appear as refuge and protection of the world. Immediately after these words the earth quaked,</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">You will appear as help and stay of the world.  (cf 29)</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>227</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">.... || In the D.-tune: || Flowers were raining from the airspace ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1 #b2 #b3 #b4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>102</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1952"/><citedRange>29</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... divine music could be heard, divine radiance flamed, and a divine</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Himmlische Musik war zu hören, es flammten himmlische Strahlen auf.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Heavenly music could be heard, heavenly rays flared up.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>119</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1952"/><citedRange>30</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">(voice) could be heard: (provided with) protection this world is now, and also in the lineage coming alive, by Śākyamuni-</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Buddhas [1.] On the earth (and in the airspace all) beings made a vow to Bṛhaddyuti: your wish may be fulfilled,</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Auf der Erde [und] (im Luftraum) wünschten alle Wesen dem Bṛhaddyuti: "Möge dein Wunsch in Erfüllung gehen, ..."</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">On the earth [and] (in the air space) all the beings were wishing to Bṛhaddyuti: "May your wish be fulfilled, ..."</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>480</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1967a"/><citedRange>66</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">you shall not despond through suffering. (You will be the protection) and shelter of the world, as the Buddha named Śākyamuni.</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">..... 1. [= 2.?] Thereupon, Bṛhaddyuti’s father, mother, wife and children</seg></seg></choice></p>
